## Why This Is Asked

Tests ability to design a policy-driven, multi-source token issuance flow with per-tenant constraints and real-time evaluation.

## Key Concepts

- Lightweight policy decision point (PDP) for token issuance
- Per-tenant audience/issuer metadata and key rotation
- Context-based access controls: IP allowlist, geolocation, time window, device fingerprint
- Caching decisions to reduce latency and load

## Code Example

```javascript
// issuance after policy approval (sketch)
function issueJWTForPolicyApproved(payload, tenant, kid, ttlSec) {
  const now = Math.floor(Date.now()/1000);
  const exp = now + ttlSec;
  const tokenPayload = {
    iss: `https://idp.example/${tenant}`,
    aud: `https://api.${tenant}.service`,
    sub: payload.sub,
    iat: now,
    exp,
    nonce: payload.nonce,
    tenant
  };
  return signJWT(tokenPayload, kid);
}
```

