## Why This Is Asked

Tests hands-on ability to bridge IdP types, enforce strict audience/issuer boundaries, and implement robust replay and revocation protections in a real-world gateway.

## Key Concepts

- SAML assertion validation and attribute mapping
- OIDC token exchange and PKCE considerations
- JWT issuance with tenant-scoped aud/iss and JWKS rotation
- Redis-backed revocation with TTLs
- Token binding: device nonce + TLS cert fingerprint to prevent replay

## Code Example

```javascript
// Issuer: extract claims, map to internal JWT
function issueInternalJwt(claims, nonce, thumbprint) {
  const payload = { sub: claims.user_id, tenant: claims.tenant, aud: claims.tenant + '.service', iss: 'internal.auth', nonce, thumbprint, scopes: claims.scopes }
  return jwt.sign(payload, keystore.getKey(), { algorithm: 'RS256', expiresIn: '15m' })
}
function verifyInternalJwt(token, expectedThumbprint) {
  const decoded = jwt.verify(token, keystore.getPublicKey(), { algorithms: ['RS256'] })
  if (decoded.thumbprint !== expectedThumbprint) throw new Error('fingerprint mismatch')
  return decoded
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

